<H3>European Agreements on Privacy</H3>
<ul>


<li>Final Text of the European Union <a 
href="http://www.privacy.org/pi/intl_orgs/ec/eudp.html">Directive on Data Protection</a> in English, French, and German and analyses. <p>


<li><a 
href="http://www.oecd.org/dsti/iccp/legal/priv-en.html">1980 Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development Guidelines on Privacy and Transborder flows</a><P>

<li><a 
href="http://www.privacy.org/pi/intl_orgs/coe/dp_convention_108.txt">1981 Council of Europe Convention For the Protection of Individuals with Regard to Automatic Processing of Personal Data</a><P>

</ul><BR>

<H3>Other European Documents</H3>
<ul>


<li>Council of Europe <A HREF = "http://www.privacy.org/pi/intl_orgs/coe/info_tech_1995.html">Recommendations</a> on Criminal Procedural Law Connected with Information Technology, 11 September 1995.<P>

<li><a 
href="http://www.cpsr.org/cpsr/privacy/privacy_international/international_laws/maastrict_title6_justice.txt">Maastrict Treaty, Title 6: Provisions on Cooperation in the Fields of Justice and Home Affairs</a><P>

<li><a 
href="http://www.privacy.org/pi/intl_orgs/schenegan_agreement.txt"> Schenegan Agreement of 14 June 1985 on abolition of border checks.</a><p>

<li><a 
href="http://www.oecd.org/dsti/iccp/legal/secur-en.html">1992 Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development Guidelines for the Security of Information Systems</a><P>
</ul>

